USPSA Match 05/24/08

I had a pretty good day may have been a little better if I would have hit the poppers with one shot.

Finished 1st in Limited and 3rd over all.

I shot my first Master Class score in Limited on Melody Line CM99-08 Calc says 85.5860%

I will have the scores posted on my sight in a couple days.

Now I am getting ready for Indiana!

BK

USPSA 7/26/09

I just could not get it together today. I was having trouble following through on shots today. I was calling misses and not even doing anything about it.(did not make them up).

I did end the day very well. I shot the match twice and the last stage I shot three times to figure out what I was doing wrong today. The first time on stage six was like 12.2? with 1 mike,the second time I had all kinds of make up shots on steel and the time was 14.??. The third run on stage 6 I shot 11.96 (15 A's and 4 C's) I just stayed with each shot which is what I should have done all day. Always good to end on a good note.

I will post results when I get them but I don't think I placed very high.

BK

I did have an insight on Smoke & Hope. While I was waiting for the buzzer I noticed I was looking at the first target but I wasn't really seeing it. It was like my eyes were glazed over sure I saw the target but it was like I wasn't focused on anything. This was happening most of the day. After I noticed this I seemed to have got it cleared up on the following stages.

I am opting not to go to a Local USPSA match on Saturday to do some well needed practice by myself at the range I will be working on some of the drills from Mike Seeklander. I am going to try to video tape some of this. I am going to really be pushing hard.(Controlled Abandon Shooting) I have to really push myself hard which I have been doing in some local matches and I am seeing improvements.

Until next time

BK

09/12/09

Had a great live fire practice session today. Did a drill from Mike Seeklander (Firing Cycle Draw and Reload) which can be found herehttp://www.shooting-performance.com/40.html I was working on follow through and getting my hits and calling my shots. I did use the timer but just for the start buzzer did not look at any times because it does not really matter I was working on the proper firing cycle and points.(well I did peak at the timer on my last run high 5 second range ) Is what really mattered was the points I did well but there is still plenty of room for improvement. I shot a total of 180 rounds on the drill and had 146 A's and 36 C's so this is a good start I wanted to be around 90-95% A's and ended up with 81% but I did call my shots!

At the end of my session I did a little experiment with the plate rack (my club needed some info on an issue is why I really did this) but anyway I was trying to shot a Plate Rack plate twice before it fell. It was kind of fun and I did not think I could do it (nor did some other folks) Well I did it a few times it was not easy at least for me. I was pretty tense because I was anticipating the second shot I knew it had to be quick.(kind of like when the buzzer goes off at a match and you start rushing) Just that feeling of tension that I had doing this was something I really haven't felt before at least not like this being able to work through that and accomplish what I wanted to do with the plate felt pretty good.

If you haven't done this give it a try you may or may not learn something. Video below of the plate rack experiment.

Until Next Time

BK

Had a steel match on 9/19/09.

I did ok not my best or worst match. I had some ups and downs. I am really struggling with this rushing thing. I get a couple good runs and then I start pushing/rushing. This is something that I am just going to have to work through. I need to get at least four consistent runs. I will be dry firing all this week and next which is something I have not done in a long time. I will be doing 15min a day just slow consistent reps.

I need to sharpen things up for my last couple major matches coming up.

There is a USPSA match next Sunday that I am not going to make but I will be live fire practicing on Saturday.

BK

Live fire practice 09/26/09

I fired 200 rounds using two different drills. It was a great session mostly A hits with some C hits and I called every shot fired. I set up a transition drill and discovered that I was not letting the gun stop on the target. I also found on the long transitions that I was not picking the exact target spot and this is why I was not stopping the gun on the target I was going past the target and had to bring the gun back to the target,problem solved after the first couple runs.

A good practice session is just what I needed before the Fall Classic next weekend. I still have a lot of room for improvement but I am on my way.

Here is a video of one of the drills I did today.

BK
